  "prompt": "What are the major aspects covered under ISO/TS 16949 Audit?",
  "response": "ISO/TS 16949 (now widely replaced by IATF 16949) is a technical specification for the automotive industry's quality management system. During an audit, several major aspects are typically covered:\n\n1. Quality Management System (QMS)\n- Documentation and record-keeping\n- Process control and standardization\n- Internal quality audits\n- Management responsibility and commitment\n\n2. Product Design and Development\n- Design review processes\n- Design validation and verification\n- Design change management\n- Risk assessment and mitigation\n\n3. Manufacturing Process Control\n- Process capability analysis\n- Statistical process control (SPC)\n- Production planning and scheduling\n- Manufacturing process documentation\n- Machine and equipment maintenance\n\n4. Customer-Specific Requirements\n- Meeting customer specifications\n- Product conformity\n- Performance monitoring\n- Complaint handling and resolution\n\n5. Supply Chain Management\n- Supplier selection and evaluation\n- Supplier performance monitoring\n- Supplier development\n- Incoming material control\n\n6. Continuous Improvement\n- Root cause analysis\n- Corrective and preventive actions\n- Performance metrics\n- Problem-solving methodologies\n\n7. Traceability and Quality Records\n- Product traceability\n- Quality documentation\n- Production history tracking\n- Inspection and test records\n\nThese aspects ensure comprehensive quality management in automotive manufacturing environments.",
